{
  "number": 840,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/840",
  "title": "Add the possibility of disabling facet values in the UI instead of removing them.",
  "body": "By design, the API only returns the facets value available for the current search context. That easily allows developers to only display the facet values that are available, and not the other. Which is very handy when the set of potential values is large, but which can also be less legible in some UX.\n\nThe idea here would be to be able to keep those facet values displayed all the time, make them look as `disabled` when those are not available for the current search context. \n\nThat would I guess be applicable to both `menu` and `refinementList` widgets.\n",
